<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>AFS0078</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:right; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">AFS0078</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Geoff </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Whitty</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-indent:18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ACADEMY CHAINS: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">SOME </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">GOVERNANCE &amp; ACCOUNTABILITY </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">ISSUES </span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">These notes arise from some work I recently undertook </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Academy Chains in Bristol</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, a highly a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cademised city</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  They are relevant to the following terms of reference for the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Committee’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inquiry:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The role of the Secretary of State in intervening in and supporting failing academies, and how this role will work as the programme expands; </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The functions and responsibilities in relation to academies and free schools of local authorities and other organi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sations operating between the Secretary of State and individual schools; what these functions and responsibilities should be; and what gaps there are in support for schools at this level;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">What role academy chains play or should play in the new school lands</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cape; how accountable they are; and what issues they raise with regard to governance arrangements. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Academies Commission identified a lack of understanding among Academy governors of their legal responsibilities.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In the case of Academy Chains, t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">may partly be because there</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> are differences in the accountability structures for Umbrella Trusts (UTs) and Multi-Academy Trusts (MATs). In UTs, the Local Governing Bodies (LGBs) remain </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">at least </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as autonomous as they are in Local Authority (LA) maintained s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">chools.  In MATs, the LGBs are effectively sub-committees of/advisory bodies to the Board of the Academy Chain. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.85pt; padding-left:3.85pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This had led to confusion in some contexts, where LGBs believe they have more (or indeed less) autonomy than they legally have.  Some Multi-A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cademy Chains have made the position clearer by renaming the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ir</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> LGBs (e.g. Academy Councils or Advisory Boards). </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There can also be confusion about whether the Chief Executive (CE) of an Academy Chain is effectively the Executive Head of its schools.  In som</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e cases, the CE line manages the local head teachers and in others does not.  In a MAT the local head teacher is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">generally </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">accountable to the Trust Board, while in a UT to the LGB.  In some cases LGBs are represented on the Trust Board, in others not.  In </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">some cases the CE is a member of the Trust Board and in others not. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.85pt; padding-left:3.85pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Clarity on such matters is important, not least in the context of Ofsted Section 5 inspections of schools, where all parties need to be clear about the differing roles of the Trust </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Board, the CE</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, the head teacher</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and the LGBs, as this will have implications for who meets with Ofsted during a school inspection</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and in what capacity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Ofsted inspectors themselves are sometimes unclear about this.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.85pt; padding-left:3.85pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector (HMCI) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is insisting that LAs should exercise </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">what he </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">regards as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">thei</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r responsibilities under the 200</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">6 Education Act across all schools in their locality including Academies.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">At the moment, their co</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mpliance is being inspected via locally </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">targeted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Section 5 inspec</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tions of schools and/or direct inspection of LA school improvement services. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Yet, even if LAs have an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> area-wide responsibility for standards, they often lack the resources or power to exercise it – especially where Academies themselves do not want them to do so.  If LAs are to be held to account for standards and school improvement in Academies (and by im</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">plication Academy Chains) the relationship between the different bodies needs clarification. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.85pt; padding-left:3.85pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">HMCI states that, if Ofsted is concerned about standards in Academies, he will write to the LA, the Academy Chain or the Secretary of State as appropriate, but i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t is unclear on what basis he decides which is appropriate. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.85pt; padding-left:3.85pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">If the LA can be inspected as a result of Ofsted’s concerns about standards in Academies in its local area, the same should surely apply to Academy Chains, which in practice usually have a greater role in challenge and support in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Academies than LAs d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o.  HMCI’s annual report has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">recently </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">indicated that a first step towards this will be taken via co-ordinated inspections of schools in under-performing chains.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">In a few cases, LAs are founding members (sponsors) of Academy Chains, in some other cases </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">they can appoint a member to the Trust Board and in still others they have membership of LGBs.  If LAs do have responsibility for standards and school improvement in their local Academies, then we need to consider the desirability and level of their repres</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">entation in the governance of Academy Chains, not least with a view to avo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">iding any conflict of interest.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There could also usefully be some clarification of who needs to be consulted if Academy Chains wish to merge. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Clearly Academy Chains are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">different from each other in size</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, structure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and geographical spread, so a one size fits all solution is unlikely to be appropriate.  However, in any particular case, there does need to be greater clarity about the governance structures and lines of respon</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">sibility than I have encountered in Bristol.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">December 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>